<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A popular South Australian almond milk has been recalled from supermarkets due to potential health risks.</p>

<p>Milk Lab Almond Milk 1L is being recalled by Rio Coffee Pty Ltd due to potential microbial contamination.</p>

<p>The milk has a best before date of August 6 2021 and has been available for purchase at cafes, supermarkets and restaurants in South Australia.</p>

<p>Milk Lab Almond Milk 1L with best before date of August 6 2021 has been recalled due to potential contamination</p>

<p>'Food products with microbial contamination may cause illness if consumed,' the recall notice reads.</p>

<p>Microbial contamination is the non-intended addition of microbes including mould, fungi, bacteria and yeast. </p>

<p>Consumers should return the product to their place of purchase to receive a full refund.</p>

<p>Those concerned about their health should seek medical advice. </p>

